        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Braised red cabbage is a low-effort, high-reward side. Two hours in a covered pot with apple and vinegar transforms a dense, raw vegetable into something silky, sweet-sour, and deeply coloured. It freezes well and improves for days after making.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
